The paper proposes a new method for unsupervised learning of predictable features from high-dimensional time series, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the relationship between the proposed method and information theory, which is a common topic in information theory and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Signal Processing). Additionally, the paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method on different datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
